MOODS AND SIGNS

      			SAD -  

 eyebrows. They will be slanting upward. A sad person will also be frowning

 				HAPPINESS - 

 large smile .

 				SURPRISE  -

 wide open eyes and an open gaping mouth
 The eyebrows will be pulled up very high.

 				FEAR - 

  The eyebrows will be slanted upward, and the eyes will be wide open.[9] The mouth might also be stretched open widely.[10]

  				DISGUST - 

 wrinkled nose 
 eyebrows will also lower, and the mouth will hang open
 upper lip will pull up.

 				ANGER - 

 eyebrows. They will be lowered and slanted inward, creasing together into a wrinkle. The eyelids will be tight and straight, as the brow will be lowered.
 The mouth may be tight, 

